# /kig-library — manage nudge sentences

Add or remove sentences the KIG monitor pulls from when nudging. Project scope by default; `--global` to affect every project. Use `suppress` to hide specific global categories, or `isolate` for a full blackout of globals in this project.

Run the backing script with the user's arguments:

```bash
~/bin/kig-library-cmd.py "$@"
```

## Subcommands

| Command | Effect |
|---|---|
| `add [--global] [--for MODES] "text"` | Add an entry (MODES comma-separated, default `all`) |
| `remove [--global] --mode MODE <N>` | Remove Nth entry from that mode's library |
| `list [--global]` | Show all entries in all three modes |
| `suppress <category-or-id>` | (project only) hide a global category/id from this project |
| `unsuppress <id>` | Undo a suppress |
| `isolate` | (project only) ignore ALL globals for this project |
| `unisolate` | Restore globals |
| `help` | This text |

## Examples

```
/kig-library add "don't commit compiled .app bundles"
/kig-library add --global --for simple "run tests before committing"
/kig-library add --for simple,verbose "this project uses Firebase Auth"
/kig-library suppress visual_verification
/kig-library isolate
```

## Scope

- **Default:** this project (`./.kig/{verbose-entries,minimal,simple,suppress}.json`, `./.kig/isolate`)
- **`--global`:** machine-wide (`~/.claude/kig/{verbose-entries,minimal,simple}.json`)
